ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W2_TrailCheck

Class Name: TrailCheck

Difficulty: Level 2 — Multi-Class Application

Estimated Time: 50 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 43 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Build a small hiking trail inspection program that manages multiple Trail objects,
updates their status based on safety scores, searches trails by name, and prints
inspection summaries.

Requirements
- Create several Trail objects.
- Store the objects in an array.
- Use TrailLog methods to print, search, count, filter, and update trails.
- Use conditionals, loops, arrays, constructors, instance methods, and String methods.
- Keep each class responsible for its own role.

Learning Objective
Practice building a small object-oriented Java program with multiple classes,
object arrays, method decomposition, condition-based state updates, and String-based search.
